Write HPA (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler) YAML
 
A Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) automatically scales the number of pods in a deployment, replica set, or stateful set based on resource metrics like CPU and memory usage.

apiVersion: autoscaling/v2
kind: HorizontalPodAutoscaler
metadata:
 name: my-app-hpa
 namespace: default
spec:
 scaleTargetRef:
 apiVersion: apps/v1
 kind: Deployment
 name: my-app # The name of the deployment to scale
 minReplicas: 2
 maxReplicas: 10
 metrics:
 - type: Resource
 resource:
 name: cpu
 target:
 type: Utilization
 averageUtilization: 50 # Scale up if average CPU usage > 50%
 - type: Resource
 resource:
 name: memory
 target:
 type: AverageValue
 averageValue: 500Mi # Scale up if average memory usage > 500Mi

1.minReplicas / maxReplicas: Defines the lower and upper boundaries for the number of pods. 

2.CPU Utilization: Targets a percentage of the pod's requested CPU. 

3.Memory Usage: Targets a specific amount of memory (e.g., 500Mi) or utilization percentage. 

Note:our cluster must have the Kubernetes Metrics Server installed to collect resource data from pods.
